               <p>JOHN BROWN. I <rs id="t18180218-113-viclabel603" type="occupation">keep the Southampton Arms, public-house</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18180218-113-victim700 t18180218-113-viclabel603"></join>, <placeName id="t18180218-113-crimeloc604">Camden Town</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18180218-113-crimeloc604" type="placeName" value="Camden Town"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18180218-113-crimeloc604" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18180218-113-off601 t18180218-113-crimeloc604"></join>. On the 18th of February I lost four pots; one from my house, and three from my different customers.</p>
               <p>JASPER SMITH. I am a constable of Bow-street. On the 18th of February, about ten o'clock in the morning, I saw the prisoner at Camden Town, and followed him to Charles-street, Hampstead-road, and asked what was in his bag - He said a bird cage. I followed him to Dyot-street, St. Giles's, where I secured him, and found his bag contained five quart and four pint pots, which were claimed by the several persons stated in the indictment.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. They were given to me to carry.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18180218-113-verdict605" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18180218-113-verdict605" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 19.</p>
